1
00:01:10,000 --> 00:01:13,000
"Double Helix"

2
00:01:16,239 --> 00:01:17,400
We've both grown up.

3
00:01:18,239 --> 00:01:19,400
We're not the same as before.

4
00:01:20,840 --> 00:01:22,079
How are we different?

5
00:01:26,079 --> 00:01:27,079
I don't love you anymore.

6
00:01:38,920 --> 00:01:39,959
Go back, Lu Feng.

7
00:01:41,000 --> 00:01:42,000
Be safe.

8
00:01:44,612 --> 00:01:45,612
It's fine.

9
00:01:47,359 --> 00:01:48,599
It's fine if you don't love me.

10
00:01:54,280 --> 00:01:55,560
We can take it slow.

11
00:01:56,853 --> 00:01:58,053
You'll learn to love me again.

12
00:02:00,000 --> 00:02:01,480
We have our whole lives ahead of us.

13
00:02:03,280 --> 00:02:04,480
We can go back.

14
00:02:05,519 --> 00:02:06,719
No matter how far we've gone.

15
00:02:08,599 --> 00:02:10,280
How can we have a lifetime?

16
00:02:13,639 --> 00:02:14,639
We'll get married.

17
00:02:15,013 --> 00:02:16,693
Once we're married, we'll have a lifetime.

18
00:02:18,000 --> 00:02:19,199
A lifetime.

19
00:02:21,439 --> 00:02:22,719
We can do anything we want.

20
00:02:24,879 --> 00:02:26,120
We can go anywhere we want.

21
00:02:28,879 --> 00:02:29,960
We can do it.

22
00:02:43,987 --> 00:02:44,987
Go back.

23
00:02:50,080 --> 00:02:51,080
Go.

24
00:02:51,360 --> 00:02:53,879
Go, go, go.

25
00:03:19,500 --> 00:03:23,500
(Episode 5: Actually, I Fell for You a Long Time Ago)

26
00:05:52,000 --> 00:05:53,879
That bastard is finally gone.

27
00:05:55,879 --> 00:05:56,879
Here.

28
00:05:59,369 --> 00:06:00,015
[From Lu Feng]

29
00:06:00,040 --> 00:06:01,040
Xiao Chen.

30
00:06:01,120 --> 00:06:02,960
I need to go back and
break off my engagement.

31
00:06:03,759 --> 00:06:04,759
Wait for me.

32
00:06:18,759 --> 00:06:20,079
Where do you get off?

33
00:06:20,399 --> 00:06:22,079
To call off the engagement on your own?

34
00:06:23,959 --> 00:06:25,519
Are you with that guy again,

35
00:06:25,759 --> 00:06:27,000
fooling around with him?

36
00:06:28,000 --> 00:06:30,079
You think just because I
let you run this company,

37
00:06:30,399 --> 00:06:32,000
that you can do whatever you want?

38
00:06:34,160 --> 00:06:35,600
His name is Cheng Yichen.

39
00:06:35,879 --> 00:06:36,879
Right?

40
00:06:39,120 --> 00:06:40,120
What are you going to do?

41
00:06:40,240 --> 00:06:41,240
I'm warning you.

42
00:06:41,399 --> 00:06:42,560
You'd better not touch him.

43
00:06:42,879 --> 00:06:43,879
You...

44
00:06:45,000 --> 00:06:46,079
Let me tell you something.

45
00:06:46,279 --> 00:06:47,720
I don't plan on touching him.

46
00:06:47,959 --> 00:06:48,959
But...

47
00:06:49,199 --> 00:06:51,439
if you continue to be this stubborn...

48
00:06:52,160 --> 00:06:53,879
Just try it and see what happens.

49
00:06:55,959 --> 00:06:56,959
You animal!

50
00:06:57,839 --> 00:06:58,919
Dad! Dad, stop hitting him!

51
00:06:59,079 --> 00:07:00,079
Dad, get out of the way!

52
00:07:00,639 --> 00:07:01,879
Dad! Dad, stop!

53
00:07:05,000 --> 00:07:06,000
Let me tell you.

54
00:07:06,240 --> 00:07:07,279
In this world,

55
00:07:07,439 --> 00:07:08,560
it's either you or him.

56
00:07:08,920 --> 00:07:10,560
If you don't break it off with him,

57
00:07:10,759 --> 00:07:13,775
I'll make him disappear
from this world immediately.

58
00:07:15,240 --> 00:07:16,000
If you dare touch him,

59
00:07:16,120 --> 00:07:17,600
you'll no longer have me as a son.

60
00:07:19,199 --> 00:07:20,199
You pushed me?

61
00:07:20,279 --> 00:07:21,279
You...

62
00:07:23,079 --> 00:07:24,079
Dad, what's wrong?

63
00:07:25,720 --> 00:07:26,560
Dad, what's wrong?

64
00:07:26,720 --> 00:07:27,399
Dad!

65
00:07:27,600 --> 00:07:29,000
Dad! Dad, what's wrong with you?

66
00:07:41,680 --> 00:07:42,879
What's wrong with him?

67
00:07:44,120 --> 00:07:45,120
A heart condition.

68
00:07:46,040 --> 00:07:47,560
He was diagnosed the year before last.

69
00:07:48,199 --> 00:07:49,399
We never told you.

70
00:08:03,439 --> 00:08:04,439
What's wrong?

71
00:08:13,160 --> 00:08:14,160
What's wrong?

72
00:08:14,279 --> 00:08:15,279
Lu Feng.

73
00:08:15,600 --> 00:08:16,600
Doctor!

74
00:08:17,399 --> 00:08:18,399
Doctor!

75
00:08:20,476 --> 00:08:22,962
[He's looking at job applications]

76
00:08:27,000 --> 00:08:27,600
Sha-sha.

77
00:08:27,759 --> 00:08:28,480
Yichen.

78
00:08:28,759 --> 00:08:29,439
Are you free?

79
00:08:29,519 --> 00:08:30,720
Could you do me a favor?

80
00:08:31,000 --> 00:08:32,000
Go ahead.

81
00:08:32,879 --> 00:08:34,399
Ever since Mr. Lu was hospitalized,

82
00:08:34,879 --> 00:08:36,375
everything at the company has been a mess.

83
00:08:36,399 --> 00:08:38,080
I'm completely swamped with work.

84
00:08:38,480 --> 00:08:40,039
I've emailed you a few tasks.

85
00:08:40,200 --> 00:08:41,240
Could you do them for me?

86
00:08:42,259 --> 00:08:43,820
Mr. Lu is in the hospital?

87
00:08:44,006 --> 00:08:45,006
Huh?

88
00:08:45,960 --> 00:08:46,960
What happened to him?

89
00:08:47,120 --> 00:08:48,879
I don't know the specifics.

90
00:08:49,279 --> 00:08:50,639
But it doesn't look good.

91
00:08:51,120 --> 00:08:52,159
Miss Lu even came back.

92
00:08:52,360 --> 00:08:54,000
She told us to keep it under wraps.

93
00:08:54,159 --> 00:08:55,655
She's afraid if something
happens to Mr. Lu,

94
00:08:55,679 --> 00:08:56,879
the stock prices will fall.

95
00:08:58,159 --> 00:08:59,159
Yichen?

96
00:08:59,559 --> 00:09:00,840
Are you listening, Yichen?

97
00:09:05,679 --> 00:09:06,480
Where are you going?

98
00:09:06,600 --> 00:09:07,680
I'm going back to Lan City.

99
00:09:08,120 --> 00:09:09,520
Why are you going back to Lan City?

100
00:09:09,559 --> 00:09:10,759
Something happened to Lu Feng.

101
00:09:11,120 --> 00:09:12,600
Why do you still care about him?

102
00:09:12,679 --> 00:09:13,679
Yi-chen.

103
00:09:13,799 --> 00:09:15,000
This time it's different.

104
00:09:15,519 --> 00:09:16,519
He might die.

105
00:09:16,799 --> 00:09:17,895
He's a living, breathing person.

106
00:09:17,919 --> 00:09:18,959
He was perfectly fine
just a couple of days ago.

107
00:09:18,960 --> 00:09:19,999
How could he just die all of a sudden?

108
00:09:20,000 --> 00:09:20,639
I don't know either.

109
00:09:20,759 --> 00:09:21,440
That's why I have to go see him.

110
00:09:21,519 --> 00:09:22,240
I'll take you.

111
00:09:22,480 --> 00:09:23,360
No, it's okay. The car I called is here.

112
00:09:23,361 --> 00:09:24,441
Then let Qin Lang take you.

113
00:09:24,559 --> 00:09:25,159
No, thanks.

114
00:09:25,160 --> 00:09:26,559
Yichen, where are you going?

115
00:09:29,279 --> 00:09:31,399
Brother, you promised you'd come back.

116
00:09:43,320 --> 00:09:44,320
Sha-sha.

117
00:09:45,159 --> 00:09:46,799
Do you know which hospital Lu Feng is in?

118
00:09:48,279 --> 00:09:48,720
Okay.

119
00:09:48,879 --> 00:09:49,360
I have to go.

120
00:09:49,399 --> 00:09:50,399
We'll talk later.

121
00:09:51,240 --> 00:09:52,559
Driver, Central Hospital.

122
00:09:52,639 --> 00:09:53,639
Please hurry.

123
00:09:57,360 --> 00:09:59,000
Doctor, how is he?

124
00:09:59,519 --> 00:10:00,720
We've done everything we can.

125
00:10:03,000 --> 00:10:04,480
Isn't there anything else you can do?

126
00:10:05,000 --> 00:10:06,160
It'll just be a few days now.

127
00:10:06,720 --> 00:10:08,639
The family should prepare yourselves.

128
00:10:15,960 --> 00:10:16,960
Miss Lu.

129
00:10:17,960 --> 00:10:18,960
I'm...

130
00:10:19,372 --> 00:10:20,453
an old friend of Lu Feng's.

131
00:10:21,039 --> 00:10:22,039
I'd like to see him.

132
00:10:23,320 --> 00:10:24,320
Cheng Yichen.

133
00:10:25,320 --> 00:10:26,399
What are you doing here?

134
00:10:28,399 --> 00:10:29,839
I just want to see him for a moment.

135
00:10:30,000 --> 00:10:31,080
And then you'll leave?

136
00:10:34,879 --> 00:10:36,199
Then you'd better just leave now.

137
00:10:36,279 --> 00:10:37,240
I just want to see him.

138
00:10:37,240 --> 00:10:37,960
I won't show up again.

139
00:10:37,961 --> 00:10:39,039
What I mean is,

140
00:10:41,086 --> 00:10:42,287
for all these years, Lu Feng

141
00:10:42,639 --> 00:10:44,159
has never given up on you.

142
00:10:44,440 --> 00:10:46,480
You either stay by his side, firmly,

143
00:10:46,679 --> 00:10:47,679
or...

144
00:10:47,720 --> 00:10:48,519
you leave and stay far away.

145
00:10:48,520 --> 00:10:50,240
Don't let him find you again. Understand?

146
00:10:54,440 --> 00:10:57,560
Do you know that I was the one who tied
my brother up and sent him to America?

147
00:11:00,360 --> 00:11:02,360
He tried to escape and
come back every single day.

148
00:11:04,159 --> 00:11:06,799
And every time, my dad would
catch him and beat him half to death.

149
00:11:08,440 --> 00:11:09,640
During the years in America,

150
00:11:10,080 --> 00:11:12,159
I hoped so much that he would forget you.

151
00:11:14,080 --> 00:11:15,119
But when he readily agreed

152
00:11:15,120 --> 00:11:16,160
to this arranged marriage,

153
00:11:16,200 --> 00:11:17,200
I knew.

154
00:11:17,480 --> 00:11:19,080
He could never forget you.

155
00:11:21,080 --> 00:11:22,080
But what about you?

156
00:11:22,519 --> 00:11:24,319
Have you ever given
him any kind of response?

157
00:11:25,440 --> 00:11:26,600
And now you show up here,

158
00:11:26,799 --> 00:11:27,799
what do you want?

159
00:11:32,480 --> 00:11:33,480
Forget it.

160
00:11:34,120 --> 00:11:35,159
If he knew you were here,

161
00:11:35,200 --> 00:11:36,200
and I didn't let you in,

162
00:11:36,799 --> 00:11:38,479
who knows what kind of tantrum he'd throw.

163
00:11:40,240 --> 00:11:41,240
Whether you go in or not

164
00:11:41,639 --> 00:11:42,759
is up to you.

165
00:12:14,519 --> 00:12:15,720
I'm sorry, Lu Feng.

166
00:12:16,519 --> 00:12:17,519
The truth is,

167
00:12:18,960 --> 00:12:21,080
I want to be with you, too.

168
00:12:30,200 --> 00:12:31,720
Am I dreaming?

169
00:12:36,360 --> 00:12:37,360
Xiao Chen.

170
00:12:39,879 --> 00:12:41,240
I'm not dreaming, am I?

171
00:13:02,679 --> 00:13:03,679
Lu Feng.

172
00:13:04,960 --> 00:13:05,960
How are you?

173
00:13:07,120 --> 00:13:08,120
I'm fine.

174
00:13:10,480 --> 00:13:12,040
How did you know I was in the hospital?

175
00:13:19,200 --> 00:13:20,200
What's wrong?

176
00:13:22,519 --> 00:13:23,519
Xiao Chen.

177
00:13:25,159 --> 00:13:26,480
Don't leave this time, okay?

178
00:13:27,840 --> 00:13:28,840
Xiao Chen.

179
00:13:30,720 --> 00:13:32,696
All these years, you're the
only one I've had in my heart.

180
00:13:32,720 --> 00:13:34,559
I came back this time just to find you.

181
00:13:36,080 --> 00:13:37,720
There's never been anyone else.

182
00:13:39,120 --> 00:13:40,120
I'm sorry.

183
00:13:42,120 --> 00:13:43,120
I was wrong.

184
00:14:00,879 --> 00:14:01,879
Lu Feng.

185
00:14:03,320 --> 00:14:05,519
You said you'd be with me for a lifetime.

186
00:14:12,240 --> 00:14:13,240
I will.

187
00:14:13,639 --> 00:14:14,919
I'll be with you for a lifetime.

188
00:14:15,279 --> 00:14:16,279
It's just...

189
00:14:17,159 --> 00:14:18,720
we should probably get married abroad.

190
00:14:20,759 --> 00:14:21,759
Lu Feng.

191
00:14:23,480 --> 00:14:27,600
Can you please live a little longer?

192
00:14:30,440 --> 00:14:31,559
I'm sorry.

193
00:14:32,679 --> 00:14:36,000
I overheard them talking at the door.

194
00:14:37,480 --> 00:14:38,480
But...

195
00:14:40,200 --> 00:14:43,159
we've been apart for over four years.

196
00:14:54,120 --> 00:14:54,720
Wait a minute.

197
00:14:54,799 --> 00:14:55,799
Wait a minute.

198
00:14:57,080 --> 00:14:59,720
You... you think I'm dying, don't you?

199
00:15:02,080 --> 00:15:03,679
When I got here,

200
00:15:04,440 --> 00:15:07,399
I heard your sister talking to the doctor.

201
00:15:08,240 --> 00:15:10,720
They said your condition wasn't good.

202
00:15:11,600 --> 00:15:13,240
That you only have a few days left.

203
00:15:18,480 --> 00:15:19,480
Stop, stop, stop.

204
00:15:19,720 --> 00:15:21,559
The one who's not
doing well... it's not me.

205
00:15:22,320 --> 00:15:23,320
It's my dad.

206
00:15:27,320 --> 00:15:30,000
My dad's heart hasn't been
doing so well these past few years.

207
00:15:31,000 --> 00:15:32,000
Yesterday...

208
00:15:32,320 --> 00:15:34,320
he found out I called off
the engagement on my own

209
00:15:34,919 --> 00:15:36,839
and that I wanted to get
back together with you.

210
00:15:37,679 --> 00:15:38,879
He got so angry he passed out.

211
00:15:39,279 --> 00:15:40,639
I'm fine, really.

212
00:15:40,879 --> 00:15:42,735
It's just... waiting for
you these past two days...

213
00:15:42,759 --> 00:15:43,759
I fainted.

214
00:15:45,120 --> 00:15:46,120
It was all my sister.

215
00:15:46,240 --> 00:15:48,240
She's the one who insisted
I stay for observation.

216
00:15:49,039 --> 00:15:50,720
Ever since Mr. Lu was hospitalized,

217
00:15:51,120 --> 00:15:52,559
the company has been in chaos.

218
00:16:06,639 --> 00:16:07,639
Cheng Yichen.

219
00:16:08,039 --> 00:16:09,399
You just promised me.

220
00:16:10,519 --> 00:16:11,519
This time...

221
00:16:12,600 --> 00:16:13,320
you're not leaving.

222
00:16:13,559 --> 00:16:14,799
You can't go back on your word.

223
00:16:16,519 --> 00:16:17,798
When you're down to your last few days,

224
00:16:17,799 --> 00:16:18,839
and ready for your coffin,

225
00:16:18,879 --> 00:16:20,216
I'll be sure to come and stay by your side.

226
00:16:20,240 --> 00:16:21,240
You liar.

227
00:16:21,840 --> 00:16:22,840
I didn't lie to you.

228
00:16:23,039 --> 00:16:24,359
You're the one who misunderstood.

229
00:16:47,200 --> 00:16:49,159
Do you really have to wait until I'm dying

230
00:16:49,600 --> 00:16:50,879
before you'll agree to stay?

231
00:16:53,360 --> 00:16:54,720
You came back to find me this time

232
00:16:55,080 --> 00:16:56,480
and said you wanted to be together.

233
00:16:57,000 --> 00:16:58,600
Is it because you really like me,

234
00:16:59,759 --> 00:17:01,120
or is it because you pity me?

235
00:17:04,319 --> 00:17:05,319
Tell me the truth.

236
00:17:11,240 --> 00:17:12,640
If you just pity me,

237
00:17:14,200 --> 00:17:15,200
then you can leave.

238
00:17:16,319 --> 00:17:17,319
I won't stop you.

239
00:17:22,759 --> 00:17:24,720
Of course I don't pity you.

240
00:17:25,680 --> 00:17:27,160
But you were so awful to me before.

241
00:17:27,680 --> 00:17:29,735
No matter how you try to
make it up to me, it's useless.

242
00:17:29,759 --> 00:17:30,959
Even if you slave away for me,

243
00:17:31,000 --> 00:17:32,319
I still might not forgive you.

244
00:17:33,640 --> 00:17:34,720
Slave away for you?

245
00:17:36,559 --> 00:17:37,559
Like this?

246
00:17:40,759 --> 00:17:43,000
Just now, I really thought
you were going to leave.

247
00:17:45,039 --> 00:17:46,319
I was so scared.

248
00:17:46,960 --> 00:17:47,960
Pervert.

249
00:17:49,920 --> 00:17:51,080
I'll show you a real pervert.

250
00:18:02,079 --> 00:18:03,079
This...

251
00:18:04,480 --> 00:18:05,480
Do you still want it?

252
00:18:30,079 --> 00:18:31,079
Xiao Chen.

253
00:18:33,960 --> 00:18:35,559
This feels so unreal.

254
00:18:37,920 --> 00:18:38,920
Does this mean we...

255
00:18:39,799 --> 00:18:41,480
can finally start over?

256
00:18:45,319 --> 00:18:46,480
Let's take it slow.

257
00:18:46,960 --> 00:18:48,360
Why did you pull out the IV needle?

258
00:18:48,559 --> 00:18:50,599
What do you think you're
doing? This is a hospital.

259
00:19:05,799 --> 00:19:07,319
Where have you been lately?

260
00:19:09,720 --> 00:19:10,880
There was a family matter.

261
00:19:11,240 --> 00:19:12,200
My leave request wasn't approved,

262
00:19:12,201 --> 00:19:13,240
so I resigned.

263
00:19:13,519 --> 00:19:14,879
Luckily, Mr. Lu didn't approve it.

264
00:19:15,119 --> 00:19:16,799
Otherwise, I'd be unemployed right now.

265
00:19:17,119 --> 00:19:19,000
Well, since you're old classmates,

266
00:19:19,160 --> 00:19:20,800
Mr. Lu would probably cut you some slack.

267
00:19:22,519 --> 00:19:23,519
Yeah, yeah.

268
00:19:23,640 --> 00:19:24,640
Let's get back to work.

269
00:19:37,160 --> 00:19:38,160
Mr. Lu just left.

270
00:19:38,799 --> 00:19:39,559
Excuse me.

271
00:19:39,759 --> 00:19:40,920
Do you know where he went?

272
00:19:41,079 --> 00:19:42,079
The hospital.

273
00:19:44,000 --> 00:19:45,440
Old Mr. Lu isn't doing well.

274
00:19:56,599 --> 00:19:57,599
Dad.

275
00:19:57,759 --> 00:19:58,799
Lu Feng is here.

276
00:20:15,519 --> 00:20:18,400
I'll ask you one last time.

277
00:20:20,640 --> 00:20:22,160
Are you...

278
00:20:23,359 --> 00:20:25,319
insistent on being with that man?

279
00:20:26,240 --> 00:20:27,400
Together?

280
00:20:40,799 --> 00:20:41,799
In my entire life,

281
00:20:43,039 --> 00:20:44,599
Cheng Yichen is the only one for me.

282
00:20:44,680 --> 00:20:45,680
Lu Feng!

283
00:20:47,759 --> 00:20:48,759
Dad!

284
00:20:50,160 --> 00:20:51,160
Then you...

285
00:20:51,480 --> 00:20:52,880
You'd better not...

286
00:20:54,119 --> 00:20:59,960
regret your decision.

287
00:21:09,440 --> 00:21:10,440
Dad!

288
00:21:11,519 --> 00:21:12,519
Dad!

289
00:21:14,119 --> 00:21:15,119
Dad!

290
00:21:16,440 --> 00:21:17,440
Dad!

291
00:21:20,200 --> 00:21:21,319
Dad!

292
00:21:22,559 --> 00:21:24,160
Dad, wake up! Dad!

293
00:21:24,640 --> 00:21:25,640
Dad!

294
00:21:30,440 --> 00:21:31,440
Dad!

295
00:21:34,200 --> 00:21:35,200
Dad!

296
00:21:39,720 --> 00:21:40,720
Dad!

297
00:21:51,079 --> 00:21:52,599
Dad had a lawyer draw up his will.

298
00:21:53,799 --> 00:21:54,960
He's giving you six months.

299
00:21:55,640 --> 00:21:56,960
Either leave the Lu family,

300
00:21:58,000 --> 00:21:59,559
or break up with Cheng Yichen.

301
00:22:02,720 --> 00:22:04,079
I'm not breaking up with him.

302
00:23:18,839 --> 00:23:20,880
This winter has been especially long.

303
00:23:22,920 --> 00:23:24,320
But it seems like it's almost over.

304
00:23:30,400 --> 00:23:31,400
Son.

305
00:23:31,440 --> 00:23:32,519
How's work been lately?

306
00:23:32,720 --> 00:23:33,720
Are you busy?

307
00:23:34,319 --> 00:23:35,319
It's okay, Mom.

308
00:23:35,559 --> 00:23:36,856
Your voice sounds a little hoarse.

309
00:23:36,880 --> 00:23:37,880
Did you catch a cold?

310
00:23:38,000 --> 00:23:39,000
It's nothing.

311
00:23:39,160 --> 00:23:40,480
Just a common cold.

312
00:23:41,640 --> 00:23:42,640
Did you go to the doctor?

313
00:23:42,880 --> 00:23:43,880
It's fine.

314
00:23:44,119 --> 00:23:45,160
It's just a minor illness.

315
00:23:45,319 --> 00:23:46,519
No need to go to the hospital.

316
00:23:46,759 --> 00:23:48,880
Remember to eat on time over there.

317
00:23:49,160 --> 00:23:50,760
And learn to cook a little for yourself.

318
00:23:50,880 --> 00:23:51,896
Don't always order takeout.

319
00:23:51,920 --> 00:23:53,160
A lot of it is unsanitary.

320
00:23:53,400 --> 00:23:54,640
Okay, I know.

321
00:23:56,519 --> 00:23:58,279
Mom, I've got something to do here.

322
00:23:58,359 --> 00:23:59,039
I have to go.

323
00:23:59,319 --> 00:24:00,319
Okay, you go ahead.

324
00:24:13,680 --> 00:24:14,680
Lu Feng.

325
00:24:14,705 --> 00:24:15,705
You're back.

326
00:24:17,279 --> 00:24:18,279
What are you doing here?

327
00:24:21,119 --> 00:24:22,400
Why did you change my curtains?

328
00:24:23,319 --> 00:24:25,000
The old ones were too poor quality.

329
00:24:25,079 --> 00:24:26,559
They couldn't even block out the sun.

330
00:24:28,279 --> 00:24:30,640
What about all this stuff?
And that stuff over there?

331
00:24:30,720 --> 00:24:31,960
They were all perfectly usable.

332
00:24:32,400 --> 00:24:35,200
That stuff was old, worn-out, and ugly.

333
00:24:35,599 --> 00:24:36,599
I threw it out.

334
00:24:37,319 --> 00:24:39,359
I also replaced the bed in
the room with a new one.

335
00:24:39,559 --> 00:24:40,656
And the towels and everything.

336
00:24:40,680 --> 00:24:43,240
Dude, this is someone else's apartment.

337
00:24:43,599 --> 00:24:46,200
Then I'll just buy it.

338
00:24:46,640 --> 00:24:48,880
You want to buy it, but
what if they don't want to sell?

339
00:24:51,079 --> 00:24:52,079
Where's my roommate?

340
00:24:54,000 --> 00:24:55,119
I had him move out.

341
00:25:07,359 --> 00:25:09,119
I know you don't want
to move into my place,

342
00:25:10,079 --> 00:25:11,400
so I had to move in here.

343
00:25:14,039 --> 00:25:15,920
Now we can be together all the time.

344
00:25:23,240 --> 00:25:24,240
Xiao Chen.

345
00:25:25,759 --> 00:25:26,799
I like you.

346
00:25:30,359 --> 00:25:32,559
That faint smile on his face...

347
00:25:33,319 --> 00:25:34,720
It was like he was shy.

348
00:25:36,720 --> 00:25:38,199
For a long, long time after,

349
00:25:38,200 --> 00:25:39,799
I remembered it clearly.

350
00:25:41,039 --> 00:25:43,319
He said it with such a confident tone.

351
00:25:45,240 --> 00:25:46,599
And at that moment,

352
00:25:48,319 --> 00:25:50,000
I truly believed him.

353
00:25:58,759 --> 00:25:59,400
Stop, stop, stop.

354
00:25:59,480 --> 00:26:00,480
Stop right here.

355
00:26:02,833 --> 00:26:03,833
We're not there yet.

356
00:26:04,240 --> 00:26:05,240
Let me repeat myself.

357
00:26:05,507 --> 00:26:07,216
Within a one-kilometer
radius of the office,

358
00:26:07,240 --> 00:26:08,279
we can't get too close.

359
00:26:08,480 --> 00:26:09,480
No holding hands.

360
00:26:09,759 --> 00:26:11,319
No talking to me alone for too long.

361
00:26:11,680 --> 00:26:13,760
No using your authority
to call me into your office.

362
00:26:13,839 --> 00:26:15,079
And no calling me Xiao Chen.

363
00:26:16,759 --> 00:26:17,599
Then just tell me,

364
00:26:17,600 --> 00:26:18,880
what can I do?

365
00:26:19,279 --> 00:26:20,519
Normal physical contact...

366
00:26:20,559 --> 00:26:21,920
No one would suspect a thing.

367
00:26:22,000 --> 00:26:22,880
Even if I hug you,

368
00:26:22,960 --> 00:26:23,960
they'll just think it's...

369
00:26:23,961 --> 00:26:25,880
affection between old classmates.

370
00:26:26,119 --> 00:26:27,400
We can't be that casual.

371
00:26:31,559 --> 00:26:32,559
Lu Feng.

372
00:26:34,720 --> 00:26:35,720
Lu Feng!

373
00:26:40,160 --> 00:26:41,160
See you in a bit.

374
00:26:47,279 --> 00:26:48,279
Drive.

375
00:27:00,160 --> 00:27:01,160
What's wrong?

376
00:27:01,400 --> 00:27:02,079
Yichen.

377
00:27:02,279 --> 00:27:03,480
Something's up with you.

378
00:27:03,839 --> 00:27:04,960
What are you talking about?

379
00:27:05,319 --> 00:27:07,799
That happy look on your face is suspicious.

380
00:27:08,440 --> 00:27:11,000
Fess up. Confession brings
leniency, resistance brings severity.

381
00:27:11,119 --> 00:27:12,160
There's nothing to tell.

382
00:27:12,599 --> 00:27:13,599
Are you going to talk?

383
00:27:16,319 --> 00:27:16,799
Well...

384
00:27:16,880 --> 00:27:18,936
Looks like I'm not getting
out of this unless I talk.

385
00:27:18,960 --> 00:27:20,319
Oh, Cheng Yichen.

386
00:27:20,519 --> 00:27:21,999
Is it a guy or a girl? Top or bottom?

387
00:27:22,960 --> 00:27:23,960
A guy.

388
00:27:24,279 --> 00:27:25,599
What's wrong with it being a guy?

389
00:27:25,960 --> 00:27:27,078
A guy like Yichen...

390
00:27:27,079 --> 00:27:29,159
is obviously the type to
attract both men and women.

391
00:27:29,839 --> 00:27:31,719
What do you mean, 'attract
both men and women'?

392
00:27:32,359 --> 00:27:33,720
Are you saying I look like a girl?

393
00:27:34,359 --> 00:27:35,359
No.

394
00:27:35,480 --> 00:27:37,038
It's because you're a man...

395
00:27:37,039 --> 00:27:38,839
that you'd attract the
interest of other men.

396
00:27:39,319 --> 00:27:41,640
I minored in gender
studies in college, you know.

397
00:27:50,720 --> 00:27:51,720
What are you doing?

398
00:27:52,680 --> 00:27:53,680
Lu Feng.

399
00:27:53,720 --> 00:27:55,079
Do you think I look...

400
00:27:55,480 --> 00:27:57,119
too delicate?

401
00:28:01,880 --> 00:28:02,880
Not at all.

402
00:28:03,640 --> 00:28:05,160
You can tell you're a man at a glance.

403
00:28:05,880 --> 00:28:08,640
But a man that other
men find very attractive.

404
00:28:12,279 --> 00:28:13,319
Actually...

405
00:28:14,039 --> 00:28:17,240
I've liked you for a very, very long time.

406
00:28:18,559 --> 00:28:19,559
How long?

407
00:28:22,480 --> 00:28:23,480
You haven't paid me yet.

408
00:28:23,599 --> 00:28:25,815
You didn't even figure out if it's a boy
or a girl, and you dare ask for money?

409
00:28:25,839 --> 00:28:26,720
I didn't even flip your stall over.

410
00:28:26,799 --> 00:28:28,519
That was me doing my good deed for the day.

411
00:28:46,599 --> 00:28:47,720
Are you okay, Cheng Yichen?

412
00:28:48,680 --> 00:28:49,359
Alright, alright.

413
00:28:49,680 --> 00:28:50,680
Let's go, let's go.

414
00:28:51,000 --> 00:28:52,095
Let's go. Class is about to start.

415
00:28:52,119 --> 00:28:53,960
Go, go, go. Move.

416
00:28:59,839 --> 00:29:00,839
Keep up.

417
00:29:02,079 --> 00:29:03,479
Pick up the pace, pick up the pace!

418
00:29:07,559 --> 00:29:08,559
No slacking!

419
00:29:11,119 --> 00:29:12,119
Bump into me.

420
00:29:12,799 --> 00:29:13,440
Bump into me. Hurry up.

421
00:29:13,480 --> 00:29:14,560
Those in the back, keep up!

422
00:29:18,160 --> 00:29:18,640
Are you okay?

423
00:29:18,641 --> 00:29:20,480
Teacher, Lu Feng is hurt!

424
00:29:21,839 --> 00:29:22,599
What happened?

425
00:29:22,680 --> 00:29:23,799
Yeah, what's wrong?

426
00:29:24,319 --> 00:29:25,856
Get him to the nurse's office, quickly.

427
00:29:25,880 --> 00:29:26,400
Who's going with him?

428
00:29:26,401 --> 00:29:28,880
Me, me, me! I'll go, I'll go, Teacher!

429
00:29:28,960 --> 00:29:29,960
Who's going with you?

430
00:29:30,759 --> 00:29:31,240
Cheng Yichen.

431
00:29:31,319 --> 00:29:32,919
You, take Lu Feng to the nurse's office.

432
00:30:02,599 --> 00:30:03,640
Wait a minute.

433
00:30:03,799 --> 00:30:06,079
If you liked me back then...

434
00:30:06,680 --> 00:30:08,118
why did you spend all of high school...

435
00:30:08,119 --> 00:30:09,240
antagonizing me?

436
00:30:12,640 --> 00:30:14,480
If you can't see, you
should donate your eyes.

437
00:30:15,960 --> 00:30:17,000
Lu Feng cursed you out?

438
00:30:17,160 --> 00:30:18,799
Yeah. He bumped into me first.

439
00:30:18,880 --> 00:30:20,295
Did you do something to piss him off?

440
00:30:20,319 --> 00:30:21,319
No.

441
00:30:21,480 --> 00:30:22,319
School's been in session for a while now...

442
00:30:22,400 --> 00:30:23,856
and I haven't even
said a single word to him.

443
00:30:23,880 --> 00:30:24,880
Let me tell you...

444
00:30:25,279 --> 00:30:26,799
you got lucky today, kid.

445
00:30:26,920 --> 00:30:27,920
Don't you know...

446
00:30:27,960 --> 00:30:29,696
he's the type to throw a
punch before saying a word.

447
00:30:29,720 --> 00:30:30,959
No one in the entire school
dares to mess with him.

448
00:30:30,960 --> 00:30:32,920
Cheng Yichen, take Lu
Feng to the nurse's office.

449
00:30:34,880 --> 00:30:36,000
Don't dawdle. Hurry up.

450
00:30:37,920 --> 00:30:39,216
Is his family in the mafia or something?

451
00:30:39,240 --> 00:30:40,240
Who knows?

452
00:30:40,359 --> 00:30:42,176
All I know is his family
is rich and powerful.

453
00:30:42,200 --> 00:30:43,200
I heard...

454
00:30:43,240 --> 00:30:44,616
that even the teachers are
afraid of getting on his bad side.

455
00:30:44,640 --> 00:30:45,559
Stop squirming.

456
00:30:45,560 --> 00:30:46,799
I'm going to drop you.

457
00:30:47,279 --> 00:30:48,480
It hurts like hell. Hurry up.

458
00:31:44,680 --> 00:31:45,720
You idiot.

459
00:31:46,240 --> 00:31:47,240
I was just trying...

460
00:31:47,559 --> 00:31:48,880
to get your attention.

461
00:31:50,799 --> 00:31:51,640
Back then...

462
00:31:51,799 --> 00:31:52,936
I'd never pursued anyone before.

463
00:31:52,960 --> 00:31:54,480
How was I supposed to know what to do?

464
00:31:58,039 --> 00:31:59,039
I think...

465
00:31:59,440 --> 00:32:01,240
we're actually pretty lucky.

466
00:32:01,839 --> 00:32:03,279
To be able, from such a young age...

467
00:32:04,759 --> 00:32:06,199
to be with the person you like...

468
00:32:07,279 --> 00:32:08,679
and stay together all this time.

469
00:32:09,640 --> 00:32:11,480
Stay together and do what?

470
00:32:13,640 --> 00:32:15,240
As long as you're by my side...

471
00:32:16,279 --> 00:32:17,599
we can do anything.

472
00:32:19,440 --> 00:32:23,240
We can eat, take walks, talk...

473
00:32:24,680 --> 00:32:25,680
sleep.

474
00:32:26,240 --> 00:32:27,279
That's so boring.

475
00:32:28,039 --> 00:32:29,559
Then do you want...

476
00:32:31,279 --> 00:32:32,759
to do something that isn't boring?

477
00:34:17,360 --> 00:34:18,880
Hello, please take a look at this.

478
00:34:54,000 --> 00:34:55,880
Why are you working yourself so hard?

479
00:35:01,800 --> 00:35:02,960
You're working hard too.

480
00:35:03,480 --> 00:35:04,519
Making noodles for me...

481
00:35:04,920 --> 00:35:06,480
washing all the dishes.

482
00:35:09,119 --> 00:35:10,119
Aren't you tired?

483
00:35:10,280 --> 00:35:11,280
It's fine.

484
00:35:14,519 --> 00:35:15,519
I'm done.

485
00:35:16,599 --> 00:35:17,599
It's too exhausting.

486
00:35:29,559 --> 00:35:31,719
I want to make lots and lots of money.

487
00:35:32,599 --> 00:35:33,599
My own money.

488
00:35:34,199 --> 00:35:35,800
My current business partners...

489
00:35:36,639 --> 00:35:38,320
are only working with me...

490
00:35:38,559 --> 00:35:40,079
out of respect for the Lu family.

491
00:35:42,480 --> 00:35:43,639
If one day...

492
00:35:44,719 --> 00:35:46,359
I'm no longer part of the Lu family...

493
00:35:47,199 --> 00:35:48,119
they wouldn't even
give me the time of day.

494
00:35:48,120 --> 00:35:49,480
Why are you putting yourself down?

495
00:35:50,239 --> 00:35:51,239
But...

496
00:35:52,440 --> 00:35:54,480
why wouldn't you
be part of the Lu family?

497
00:35:54,666 --> 00:35:56,666
With your abilities, you'd
succeed at anything.

498
00:35:56,760 --> 00:35:57,960
But as for the future...

499
00:35:58,480 --> 00:35:59,560
no one can say for sure.

500
00:36:03,840 --> 00:36:05,000
If one day...

501
00:36:05,199 --> 00:36:07,000
I really become a penniless nobody...

502
00:36:08,039 --> 00:36:09,359
and have absolutely nothing...

503
00:36:10,440 --> 00:36:11,440
would you...

504
00:36:13,119 --> 00:36:14,679
leave me?

505
00:36:15,920 --> 00:36:16,920
What?

506
00:36:17,119 --> 00:36:18,479
Am I only with you for your money?

507
00:36:20,800 --> 00:36:22,079
That's not what I meant.

508
00:36:24,480 --> 00:36:25,719
I just don't know...

509
00:36:26,559 --> 00:36:27,760
what I should do...

510
00:36:29,880 --> 00:36:31,400
to make you happier.

511
00:36:33,039 --> 00:36:34,159
To help you...

512
00:36:36,039 --> 00:36:37,039
live a better life.

513
00:36:38,639 --> 00:36:40,000
I worry every day...

514
00:36:40,119 --> 00:36:41,319
that when you're with me...

515
00:36:42,400 --> 00:36:43,880
you might not be happy.

516
00:36:45,119 --> 00:36:46,159
That you might...

517
00:36:46,760 --> 00:36:49,000
suddenly feel one day...

518
00:36:49,639 --> 00:36:51,199
that I'm a very boring person.

519
00:36:51,559 --> 00:36:52,559
Are you stupid?

520
00:36:52,719 --> 00:36:54,359
When have I ever thought you were boring?

521
00:36:54,920 --> 00:36:56,359
It's because you never say anything...

522
00:36:56,360 --> 00:36:57,679
that I get scared.

523
00:37:06,880 --> 00:37:07,880
You know?

524
00:37:09,039 --> 00:37:10,039
The truth is...

525
00:37:11,000 --> 00:37:12,199
most of the time...

526
00:37:13,119 --> 00:37:17,239
I have no idea what
you're really thinking.

527
00:37:19,239 --> 00:37:20,239
It's like...

528
00:37:20,400 --> 00:37:21,400
right now...

529
00:37:22,559 --> 00:37:23,880
do you really like me?

530
00:37:25,360 --> 00:37:27,159
In my heart, I'm not sure at all.

531
00:37:30,320 --> 00:37:31,320
And you...

532
00:37:31,480 --> 00:37:33,320
even when you don't
want to do something...

533
00:37:33,960 --> 00:37:35,000
you'll still have

534
00:37:35,280 --> 00:37:36,280
'Okay'

535
00:37:36,400 --> 00:37:37,400
and 'It's fine'

536
00:37:37,800 --> 00:37:38,840
on the tip of your tongue.

537
00:37:43,239 --> 00:37:45,159
Just like when we were
eating noodles earlier.

538
00:37:46,079 --> 00:37:47,719
You clearly had something to tell me.

539
00:37:48,000 --> 00:37:49,000
By the way...

540
00:37:49,239 --> 00:37:50,400
are you busy on Friday?

541
00:37:50,480 --> 00:37:52,400
This Friday, I have to fly to LA.

542
00:37:52,719 --> 00:37:54,256
I have an international
conference to attend.

543
00:37:54,280 --> 00:37:55,280
Why?

544
00:37:58,519 --> 00:37:59,519
Nothing.

545
00:38:01,679 --> 00:38:02,679
It's really nothing?

546
00:38:08,519 --> 00:38:10,280
You clearly had something to tell me.

547
00:38:11,039 --> 00:38:12,199
When I asked you...

548
00:38:12,880 --> 00:38:14,160
you just said it was nothing.

549
00:38:14,199 --> 00:38:15,639
Why wouldn't you tell me?

550
00:38:17,599 --> 00:38:19,000
Am I that untrustworthy?

551
00:38:19,400 --> 00:38:20,400
I...

552
00:38:24,360 --> 00:38:25,400
I wanted...

553
00:38:26,719 --> 00:38:28,479
to celebrate Green
Valentine's Day with you.

554
00:38:37,119 --> 00:38:38,480
What kind of holiday is that?

555
00:38:43,039 --> 00:38:44,679
It's because we've never celebrated it...

556
00:38:45,239 --> 00:38:47,079
that we should
celebrate every one we can.

557
00:38:51,440 --> 00:38:53,159
How can you be so cute?

558
00:38:54,039 --> 00:38:55,480
I'm just going for a meeting.

559
00:38:56,519 --> 00:38:57,959
It's not like I'm never coming back.

560
00:38:58,719 --> 00:38:59,800
If you want to celebrate...

561
00:39:00,920 --> 00:39:02,800
I can fly back to celebrate with you.

562
00:39:03,400 --> 00:39:04,480
But you didn't say so.

563
00:39:04,559 --> 00:39:06,360
I should be the one saying that to you.

564
00:39:14,039 --> 00:39:15,039
Lu Feng.

565
00:39:16,760 --> 00:39:17,960
I want to tell you...

566
00:39:20,800 --> 00:39:21,880
I don't want a car...

567
00:39:23,280 --> 00:39:24,320
or a house...

568
00:39:25,880 --> 00:39:27,719
or any expensive gifts.

569
00:39:28,559 --> 00:39:29,559
I just want...

570
00:39:30,360 --> 00:39:32,320
you to spend a little more time with me.

571
00:39:34,039 --> 00:39:36,000
In the future, even if you have nothing...

572
00:39:36,360 --> 00:39:37,560
and are completely broke...

573
00:39:39,000 --> 00:39:40,639
I'll still be by your side.

574
00:39:42,119 --> 00:39:43,919
Even if you don't have
money in the future...

575
00:39:44,840 --> 00:39:46,159
I can still support you.

576
00:39:50,599 --> 00:39:51,639
Silly.

577
00:39:53,360 --> 00:39:55,120
How could I possibly
need you to support me?

578
00:39:57,400 --> 00:39:59,480
I'm the one who wants to
support you for a lifetime.

579
00:40:38,719 --> 00:40:40,119
Wait for me to come back on Friday.

580
00:40:45,559 --> 00:40:46,559
Okay.

581
00:40:58,280 --> 00:40:59,000
Yichen.

582
00:40:59,119 --> 00:41:00,039
Bring your girlfriend...

583
00:41:00,040 --> 00:41:02,200
and let's go have fun at
the Green Valnetine's Day event.

584
00:41:04,400 --> 00:41:05,400
Um...

585
00:41:05,840 --> 00:41:06,920
they're on a business trip.

586
00:41:07,280 --> 00:41:08,920
A business trip on such an important day?

587
00:41:09,320 --> 00:41:10,320
Then let's go together.

588
00:41:11,559 --> 00:41:12,879
I don't want to be a third wheel.

589
00:41:13,000 --> 00:41:14,000
I'm gonna go.

590
00:41:16,400 --> 00:41:18,000
Why'd he run off faster than a rabbit?

591
00:41:19,039 --> 00:41:20,039
So, should we go?

592
00:41:20,239 --> 00:41:21,239
Get off.

593
00:41:21,840 --> 00:41:22,840
That Cheng Yichen...

594
00:41:22,960 --> 00:41:25,320
I'm going to find his
girlfriend tonight no matter what.

595
00:41:25,639 --> 00:41:26,639
What are you going to do?

596
00:41:26,840 --> 00:41:27,719
Let's go grocery shopping.

597
00:41:27,840 --> 00:41:29,840
We're celebrating at Cheng
Yichen's house tonight.

598
00:41:37,159 --> 00:41:38,159
Lu Feng.

599
00:41:39,199 --> 00:41:40,199
Lu Feng.

600
00:41:43,599 --> 00:41:45,000
Lu Feng, Lu Feng.

601
00:41:46,360 --> 00:41:47,719
You missed me that much, huh?

602
00:41:50,840 --> 00:41:51,840
I love you.

603
00:41:55,239 --> 00:41:56,559
I love you more.

604
00:41:59,039 --> 00:42:00,400
How much do you love me?

605
00:42:02,320 --> 00:42:03,559
Well...

606
00:42:04,320 --> 00:42:05,320
More than you.

607
00:42:07,559 --> 00:42:08,559
Then...

608
00:42:09,840 --> 00:42:12,280
let me be on top for once.

609
00:42:13,039 --> 00:42:14,079
How about it?

610
00:42:18,639 --> 00:42:19,639
No way.

611
00:42:20,559 --> 00:42:21,280
Why?

612
00:42:21,281 --> 00:42:22,880
How come you can but I can't?

613
00:42:23,719 --> 00:42:26,000
You'll have to overpower me first.

614
00:42:27,159 --> 00:42:28,159
That's not fair.

615
00:42:28,519 --> 00:42:29,719
We're both men.

616
00:42:29,840 --> 00:42:31,559
Why do I always have to be on the bottom?

617
00:42:32,000 --> 00:42:33,599
You just said you loved me.

618
00:42:33,760 --> 00:42:36,000
And you can't even do
this one little thing for me?

619
00:42:36,440 --> 00:42:37,960
You don't love me at all.

620
00:42:53,760 --> 00:42:54,960
Fine. You can top once.

621
00:42:56,559 --> 00:42:57,559
Just once.

622
00:42:58,280 --> 00:42:59,280
Oh, Feng...

623
00:42:59,760 --> 00:43:00,559
I knew it.

624
00:43:00,639 --> 00:43:02,000
You're the best.

625
00:43:10,760 --> 00:43:12,239
Can we take a rain check?

626
00:43:13,719 --> 00:43:14,400
I already said.

627
00:43:14,559 --> 00:43:15,599
You only get one chance.

628
00:43:19,159 --> 00:43:20,159
Who is it?

629
00:43:21,880 --> 00:43:22,880
There goes your chance.

630
00:43:23,039 --> 00:43:24,039
Who is it?

631
00:43:24,239 --> 00:43:25,280
What's going on?

632
00:43:26,599 --> 00:43:27,280
What's that noise?

633
00:43:27,400 --> 00:43:28,440
Your girlfriend is inside.

634
00:43:28,880 --> 00:43:29,880
What?

635
00:43:30,960 --> 00:43:32,480
Well, well, Cheng Yichen.

636
00:43:33,480 --> 00:43:34,678
Hiding a secret lover, are we?

637
00:43:34,679 --> 00:43:35,679
Who is it?
